<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="multiple_cloning_site_mcs">Multiple Cloning Site (MCS)</a> - A designed stretch of <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a> with recognition sites for many common <a href="#restriction_enzyme">restriction enzymes</a>. This region allows for the easy design, management, and <a href="#cloning_molecular_cloning">cloning</a> of <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a> into larger environments, such as <a href="#plasmid">plasmids</a>.